A Christmas attraction designed by TV presenter Laurence Llewelyn-Bowen went bust - owing creditors nearly £1million.

The Magical Journey, based at the Belfry Hotel, in Sutton Coldfield, Birmingham, was marred with controversy before closing just nine days before Christmas - leaving furious parents out of pocket.

Liquidators hired to handle the firm said creditors are owed in the region of £875,000 following the early closure of the attraction, which cost upwards of £50 for a family of three.

